signatureAbility.signatureDescription: A surehanded receiver is a quarterback's best friend. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate (and decreases knockout chance) on possession catches.
Ballcarriers with this ability have more powerful truck and stiff arm animations and a larger timing window for perfect attempts.
Ballcarriers with this ability retain more of their forward momentum during tackles while travelling at high speeds.
Ballcarriers with this ability are effective at recovering from attempted tackles regardless of their current stamina.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in any mid-field zone coverage, less than 20 yards from the LoS inside the numbers and 10-20 outside.
Players with this ability are more likely to succeed at and attempt diving catches and swats.
Defenders with this ability will have full vision of plays the offense has run a scaling number of times each quarter, via coach cam.
Blockers with this ability will frequently attempt and win impact blocks against linebackers and defensive backs when playing as a lineman or fullback.
